cli/README.md
     1вҶ’# Command-line tool
     3вҶ’The `mdbook` command-line tool is used to create and build books.
     4вҶ’After you have [installed](../guide/installation.md) `mdbook`, you can run the `mdbook help` command in your terminal to view the available commands.
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’This following sections provide in-depth information on the different commands available.
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’* [`mdbook init <directory>`](init.md) --- Creates a new book with minimal boilerplate to start with.
     9вҶ’* [`mdbook build`](build.md) --- Renders the book.
    10вҶ’* [`mdbook watch`](watch.md) --- Rebuilds the book any time a source file changes.
    11вҶ’* [`mdbook serve`](serve.md) --- Runs a web server to view the book, and rebuilds on changes.
    12вҶ’* [`mdbook test`](test.md) --- Tests Rust code samples.
    13вҶ’* [`mdbook clean`](clean.md) --- Deletes the rendered output.
    14вҶ’* [`mdbook completions`](completions.md) --- Support for shell auto-completion.
