continuous-integration.md
     1вҶ’# Running `mdbook` in continuous integration
     3вҶ’There are a variety of services such as [GitHub Actions] or [GitLab CI/CD] which can be used to test and deploy your book automatically.
     4вҶ’
     5вҶ’The following provides some general guidelines on how to configure your service to run mdBook.
     6вҶ’Specific recipes can be found at the [Automated Deployment] wiki page.
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’[GitHub Actions]: https://docs.github.com/en/actions
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    12вҶ’## Installing mdBook
    14вҶ’There are several different strategies for installing mdBook.
    15вҶ’The particular method depends on your needs and preferences.
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’### Pre-compiled binaries
    19вҶ’Perhaps the easiest method is to use the pre-compiled binaries found on the [GitHub Releases page][releases].
    20вҶ’A simple approach would be to use the popular `curl` CLI tool to download the executable:
    21вҶ’
    22вҶ’```sh
    23вҶ’mkdir bin
    24вҶ’curl -sSL https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/releases/download/{{ mdbook-version }}/mdbook-{{ mdbook-version }}-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz | tar -xz --directory=bin
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    39вҶ’### Building from source
    41вҶ’Building from source will require having Rust installed.
    42вҶ’Some services have Rust pre-installed, but if your service does not, you will need to add a step to install it.
    43вҶ’
    44вҶ’After Rust is installed, `cargo install` can be used to build and install mdBook.
    45вҶ’We recommend using a SemVer version specifier so that you get the latest **non-breaking** version of mdBook.
    46вҶ’For example:
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    67вҶ’## Running tests
    69вҶ’You may want to run tests using [`mdbook test`] every time you push a change or create a pull request.
    70вҶ’This can be used to validate Rust code examples in the book.
    71вҶ’
    72вҶ’This will require having Rust installed.
    73вҶ’Some services have Rust pre-installed, but if your service does not, you will need to add a step to install it.
    74вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    83вҶ’## Deploying
    85вҶ’You may want to automatically deploy your book.
    86вҶ’Some may want to do this every time a change is pushed, and others may want to only deploy when a specific release is tagged.
    87вҶ’
    88вҶ’You'll also need to understand the specifics on how to push a change to your web service.
    89вҶ’For example, [GitHub Pages] just requires committing the output onto a specific git branch.
    90вҶ’Other services may require using something like SSH to connect to a remote server.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   100вҶ’### 404 handling
   102вҶ’mdBook automatically generates a 404 page to be used for broken links.
   103вҶ’The default output is a file named `404.html` at the root of the book.
   104вҶ’Some services like [GitHub Pages] will automatically use this page for broken links.
   105вҶ’For other services, you may want to consider configuring the web server to use this page as it will provide the reader navigation to get back to the book.
   106вҶ’
   107вҶ’If your book is not deployed at the root of the domain, then you should set the [`output.html.site-url`] setting so that the 404 page works correctly.
