for_developers/README.md
     1вҶ’# For developers
     3вҶ’While `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4вҶ’underlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5вҶ’flexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6вҶ’consumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7вҶ’the book or render it in a different format.
     8вҶ’
     9вҶ’The *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10вҶ’`mdbook`.
    11вҶ’
    12вҶ’The two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13вҶ’
    14вҶ’- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15вҶ’- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’## The build process
    19вҶ’The process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20вҶ’
    21вҶ’1. Load the book
    22вҶ’    - Parse the `book.toml`, falling back to the default `Config` if it doesn't
    23вҶ’       exist
    24вҶ’    - Load the book chapters into memory
    25вҶ’    - Discover which preprocessors/backends should be used
    26вҶ’2. For each backend:
    27вҶ’   1. Run all the preprocessors.
    28вҶ’   2. Call the backend to render the processed result.
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’## Using `mdbook` as a library
    32вҶ’The `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33вҶ’exposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34вҶ’programmatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
    35вҶ’This can be used to add your own functionality or tweak the build process.
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’The easiest way to find out how to use the `mdbook-driver` crate is by looking at the
    38вҶ’[API Docs]. The top level documentation explains how one would use the
    39вҶ’[`MDBook`] type to load and build a book, while the [config] module gives a good
    40вҶ’explanation on the configuration system.
    41вҶ’
    42вҶ’[`MDBook`]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/struct.MDBook.html
    43вҶ’[API Docs]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/
    44вҶ’[config]: https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/config/index.html
for_developers/backends.md
     1вҶ’# Alternative backends
     3вҶ’A "backend" is simply a program which `mdbook` will invoke during the book
     4вҶ’rendering process. This program is passed a JSON representation of the book and
     5вҶ’configuration information via `stdin`. Once the backend receives this
     6вҶ’information it is free to do whatever it wants.
     7вҶ’
