format/mdbook.md
     1вҶ’# mdBook-specific features вҖҰ
     3вҶ’## Hiding code lines
     5вҶ’There is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’For the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8вҶ’This prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11вҶ’
    12вҶ’```bash
    13вҶ’# fn main() {
    14вҶ’    let x = 5;
    15вҶ’    let y = 6;
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’    println!("{}", x + y);
    18вҶ’# }
    19вҶ’```
    20вҶ’
    21вҶ’Will render as
    22вҶ’
    23вҶ’```rust
    24вҶ’# fn main() {
    25вҶ’    let x = 5;
    26вҶ’    let y = 6;
    27вҶ’
    28вҶ’    println!("{}", x + y);
    29вҶ’# }
    30вҶ’```
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’When you tap or hover the mouse over the code block, there will be an eyeball icon (<i class="fa fa-eye"></i>) which will toggle the visibility of the hidden lines.
    33вҶ’
    34вҶ’By default, this only works for code examples that are annotated with `rust`.
    35вҶ’However, you can define custom prefixes for other languages by adding a new line-hiding prefix in your `book.toml` with the language name and prefix character(s):
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’```toml
    38вҶ’[output.html.code.hidelines]
    39вҶ’python = "~"
    40вҶ’```
    41вҶ’
    42вҶ’The prefix will hide any lines that begin with the given prefix. With the python prefix shown above, this:
    43вҶ’
    44вҶ’```bash
    45вҶ’~hidden()
    46вҶ’nothidden():
    47вҶ’~    hidden()
    48вҶ’    ~hidden()
    49вҶ’    nothidden()
    50вҶ’```
    51вҶ’
    52вҶ’will render as
    53вҶ’
    54вҶ’```python
    55вҶ’~hidden()
    56вҶ’nothidden():
    57вҶ’~    hidden()
    58вҶ’    ~hidden()
    59вҶ’    nothidden()
    60вҶ’```
    61вҶ’
    62вҶ’This behavior can be overridden locally with a different prefix. This has the same effect as above:
    63вҶ’
    64вҶ’~~~markdown
    65вҶ’```python,hidelines=!!!
    66вҶ’!!!hidden()
    67вҶ’nothidden():
    68вҶ’!!!    hidden()
    69вҶ’    !!!hidden()
    70вҶ’    nothidden()
    71вҶ’```
    72вҶ’~~~
    73вҶ’
