format/theme/README.md
     1вҶ’# Theme
     3вҶ’The default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4вҶ’render your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5вҶ’binary.
     6вҶ’
     7вҶ’The theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8вҶ’the theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9вҶ’project root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10вҶ’and now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11вҶ’
    12вҶ’Here are the files you can override:
    13вҶ’
    14вҶ’- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
    15вҶ’- **_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section.
    16вҶ’- **_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page.
    17вҶ’- **_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book.
    18вҶ’    - **_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements.
    19вҶ’    - **_css/general.css_** is the base styles.
    20вҶ’    - **_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output.
    21вҶ’    - **_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files.
    22вҶ’- **_book.js_** is mostly used to add client side functionality, like hiding /
    23вҶ’  un-hiding the sidebar, changing the theme, ...
    24вҶ’- **_highlight.js_** is the JavaScript that is used to highlight code snippets,
    25вҶ’  you should not need to modify this.
    26вҶ’- **_highlight.css_** is the theme used for the code highlighting.
    27вҶ’- **_favicon.svg_** and **_favicon.png_** the favicon that will be used. The SVG
    28вҶ’  version is used by [newer browsers].
    29вҶ’- **fonts/fonts.css** contains the definition of which fonts to load.
    30вҶ’  Custom fonts can be included in the `fonts` directory.
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’Generally, when you want to tweak the theme, you don't need to override all the
    33вҶ’files. If you only need changes in the stylesheet, there is no point in
    34вҶ’overriding all the other files. Because custom files take precedence over
    35вҶ’built-in ones, they will not get updated with new fixes / features.
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’**Note:** When you override a file, it is possible that you break some
    38вҶ’functionality. Therefore I recommend to use the file from the default theme as
    39вҶ’template and only add / modify what you need. You can copy the default theme
    40вҶ’into your source directory automatically by using `mdbook init --theme` and just
    41вҶ’remove the files you don't want to override.
    42вҶ’
    43вҶ’`mdbook init --theme` will not create every file listed above.
    44вҶ’Some files, such as `head.hbs`, do not have built-in equivalents.
    45вҶ’Just create the file if you need it.
    46вҶ’
    47вҶ’If you completely replace all built-in themes, be sure to also set
    48вҶ’[`output.html.preferred-dark-theme`] in the config, which defaults to the
    49вҶ’built-in `navy` theme.
    50вҶ’
    51вҶ’[`output.html.preferred-dark-theme`]: ../configuration/renderers.md#html-renderer-options
    52вҶ’[newer browsers]: https://caniuse.com/#feat=link-icon-svg
