guide/creating.md
     1вҶ’# Creating a book
     3вҶ’Once you have the `mdbook` CLI tool installed, you can use it to create and render a book.
     4вҶ’
     5вҶ’## Initializing a book
     7вҶ’The `mdbook init` command will create a new directory containing an empty book for you to get started.
     8вҶ’Give it the name of the directory that you want to create:
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    32вҶ’## Anatomy of a book
    34вҶ’A book is built from several files which define the settings and layout of the book.
    35вҶ’
    36вҶ’### `book.toml`
    38вҶ’In the root of your book, there is a `book.toml` file which contains settings for describing how to build your book.
    39вҶ’This is written in the [TOML markup language](https://toml.io/).
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    50вҶ’### `SUMMARY.md`
    52вҶ’The next major part of a book is the summary file located at `src/SUMMARY.md`.
    53вҶ’This file contains a list of all the chapters in the book.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    73вҶ’### Source files
    75вҶ’The content of your book is all contained in the `src` directory.
    76вҶ’Each chapter is a separate Markdown file.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    96вҶ’## Publishing a book
    98вҶ’Once you've written your book, you may want to host it somewhere for others to view.
    99вҶ’The first step is to build the output of the book.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
guide/installation.md
     1вҶ’# Installation
     3вҶ’There are multiple ways to install the mdBook CLI tool.
     4вҶ’Choose any one of the methods below that best suit your needs.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
     9вҶ’## Pre-compiled binaries
    11вҶ’Executable binaries are available for download on the [GitHub Releases page][releases].
    12вҶ’Download the binary for your platform (Windows, macOS, or Linux) and extract the archive.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    19вҶ’## Build from source using Rust
    21вҶ’To build the `mdbook` executable from source, you will first need to install Rust and Cargo.
    22вҶ’Follow the instructions on the [Rust installation page].
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    41вҶ’### Installing the latest master version
    43вҶ’The version published to crates.io will ever so slightly be behind the version hosted on GitHub.
    44вҶ’If you need the latest version you can build the git version of mdBook yourself.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    53вҶ’## Modifying and contributing
    55вҶ’If you are interested in making modifications to mdBook itself, check out the [Contributing Guide] for more information.
    56вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
guide/reading.md
     1вҶ’# Reading books
     3вҶ’This chapter gives an introduction on how to interact with a book produced by mdBook.
     4вҶ’This assumes you are reading an HTML book.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    12вҶ’## Navigation
    14вҶ’There are several methods for navigating through the chapters of a book.
    15вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    26вҶ’## Top menu bar
    28вҶ’The menu bar at the top of the page provides some icons for interacting with the book.
    29вҶ’The icons displayed will depend on the settings of how the book was generated.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    42вҶ’## Search
    44вҶ’Each book has a built-in search system.
    45вҶ’Pressing the search icon <i class="fas fa-magnifying-glass"></i> in the menu bar, or pressing the <kbd>/</kbd> or <kbd>S</kbd> key on the keyboard will open an input box for entering search terms.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    54вҶ’## Code blocks
    56вҶ’mdBook books are often used for programming projects, and thus support highlighting code blocks and samples.
    57вҶ’Code blocks may contain several different icons for interacting with them:
      вҶ’вҖҰ
